 * testSize                                     [ TODO ]
 * testClear                                    [ TODO ]
 * testOperatorPlus                             [ TODO ]

+---------------------------+
|    SUMMARY                |
+---------------------------+
|  SUCCESS  :    0 (  0 %)  |
|  INDEV    :    0 (  0 %)  |
|  TODO     :    3 (100 %)  |
|  FAILED   :    0 (  0 %)  |
|  UNKNOWN  :    0 (  0 %)  |
+---------------------------+
|  TOTAL    :    3          |
|  STATUS   : TODO          |
+---------------------------+
@endverbatim

You can filter the tests to execute by using :

@code
./testString -a ::testSize -a ::testClear
@endcode

So you get : 
@verbatim
